500|$|In the United States the Christian Science {{church has}} persuaded {{federal and local}} {{government}} to create and maintain religious-exemption statutes, using the <b>Free</b> <b>Exercise</b> Clause <b>of</b> the First Amendment. The <b>Free</b> <b>Exercise</b> Clause (italicized) reads: [...] "Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion, or prohibiting the <b>free</b> <b>exercise</b> thereof...." [...] Many of the exemptions say that in life-threatening situations children must have access to medical care, but without early access the seriousness of an illness may not be recognized, in part because Christian Scientists are discouraged from educating themselves about physical ailments.|$|R
